    "In Proceedings of the 13th International Joint Conference on Natural A.1.3 Scope: Local or Global This categorization is based on the scope of the explanation: local or global.",
    "A local explanation describes the mechanism for an individual instance.",
    "For example, feature attributions and attention visualizations (§B.1).",
    "Conversely, global explanations describe the mechanism for the entire data distribution, for example, probing (§B.2) and mechanistic interpretability (§B.3).",
    "Many local explanations can be generalized into global ones."
  ],
